<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">&quot;Go into all the world and preach the good news to all creation.  Whoever believes and is baptized will be saved, but whoever does not believe will be condemned.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Mark 16:15-16<br>
<br>
Jesus said that those who believe and are baptized will be saved.  He doesn't say there are any other requirements to be saved or any other ways to be saved.  For as Paul wrote later:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>For it is by grace you have been saved, through faith - and this not from yourselves, it is the gift of God - not by works, so that no one can boast.  For we are God's workmanship, created in Christ Jesus to do good works, which God prepared in advance for us to do.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Eph. 2:8-10<br>
<br>
Everywhere in the New Testament, the Bible says to be a Christian is to believe.  It often says believe and be baptized.  Now the Bible talks about us doing good works and living our life as Christ commanded us to - such as forgiving others and showing mercy.  However, they do not save us and no where in the Bible does it say such acts will save a person.  But the Bible makes it clear that we are saved only by accepting salvation freely.  The good works such as forgiveness and showing mercy come after we have been saved by grace through Christ.  As we grow, as we mature, as we learn and understand God better and what He wants of us - good works result from our love of Him and our knowledge and understanding of the kind of life He wants us to lead.  Our good works result from our love and loyalty to Him.  When people simply do good deeds who do not know Jesus, they are not doing it for the Lord.  Who knows why they're doing it, perhaps there is enough of God's essence in the world that it affects the lost unknowingly, but it doesn't save them.  They have to acknowledge Jesus first, or their good works are worthless.  Good works don't save us.  And certainly people who do not know Jesus - they're not saved.  The Bible is clear, you have to acknowledge Jesus to be saved.<br>
<br>
James talks about how faith without works is dead.  I don't think he ever mentioned works without faith.  Why?  Because without the faith in Jesus, you can't be saved period.  Faith has to be there.  You have to know who Jesus is and believe Him to be true. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">**********************************************<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Suppose this black pit of a kingdom of yours is the only world.  Well, it strikes me as a pretty poor one.  And that's a funny thing, when you come to think of it.  We're just babies making up a game, if you're right.  But four babies playing a game can make a play-world which licks your real world hollow.&quot; - Puddleglum (The Silver Chair)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeffthefinn>jeffthefinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/finnbutton.GIF" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Your Friendly<br>Orthodox Resource</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#B87333>(9/10/03 2:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/jfinn.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who are the children of God?</span><hr size=1> So you disagree with what Our Lord taught?  He who forgives will be forgiven?  St Paul said to work out your salvation with fear and trembling, why?  <br>
If you live a life of forgiving and showing mercy, you believe, if you believe and do not do that you do not believe.  Faith without works is dead, because you can not have faith without them.  <br>
The Kingdom of God is a way of life, not a belief system.  Narrow is the Way that leads to eternal life and few are they that find it, said our Lord.<br>
What is being saved?  Is being saved, an escape from hell?  Or is it something much more?  <br>
In Matthew 25 the questions asked at the judgement have nothing to do with belief systems but with mercy and showing mercy.  <br>
James 2:13 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>For judgment is merciless for the one who has shown no mercy. But mercy triumphs over judgment.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
If Our Lord forgives someone is that person saved?  Because He said he who forgives will be forgiven.<br>
Jeff the Finn<br>
