95znsFWsdG3hqkZ837sBeDrkWiqeqryPo/hpavatar.jp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who are the children of God?</span><hr size=1> I know people who forgive and show mercy and reject Jesus.  Are you telling me they are saved even though they willfully reject Jesus?  I don't disagree with what the Bible says.  The Bible says, as I have already quoted, that to be saved means to accept the free gift and can not be earned by works.  Why do you not respond to the verses I have quoted? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">**********************************************<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Suppose this black pit of a kingdom of yours is the only world.  Well, it strikes me as a pretty poor one.  And that's a funny thing, when you come to think of it.  We're just babies making up a game, if you're right.  But four babies playing a game can make a play-world which licks your real world hollow.&quot; - Puddleglum (The Silver Chair)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeffthefinn>jeffthefinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/finnbutton.GIF" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Your Friendly<br>Orthodox Resource</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#B87333>(9/10/03 5:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/jfinn.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who are the children of God?</span><hr size=1> How does one reject Jesus?  <br>
Matthew 21:28-32<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“What do you think? A man had two sons. He went to the first and said, ‘Son, go and work in the vineyard today.’ The boy answered, ‘I will not.’ But later he had a change of heart and went.  The father went to the other son and said the same thing. This boy answered, ‘I will, sir,’ but did not go.  Which of the two did his father’s will?” They said, “The first.” Jesus said to them, “I tell you the truth, tax collectors and prostitutes will go ahead of you into the kingdom of God!  For John came to you in the way of righteousness, and you did not believe him. But the tax collectors and prostitutes did believe. Although you saw this, you did not later change your minds and believe him.&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Here is you answer from Our Lord, about who does the Will of the Father.  The one who says I will and does not do it, or the son who says I will not and does it?  Jesus is less interested in verbal agreement and then with the fruit of doing the will of the Father.  <br>
By their fruits you shall know them, and someone who is forgiving and merciful is doing the will of the Father.<br>
You have not answered what being saved is.  Salvation is granted to everyone period, everyone is forgiven and given life because of the Great and Holy Pascha of Our Lord.  Not all people want that and some will actively reject being loved and forgiven.  But you will know that by how they live and on what choices they make about their life.  Jesus said, where your treasure is; there is where your heart is.<br>
Our Lord is very clear, those who do not do what he says are those on the broad way that leads to destruction, but those who forgive and show mercy are on the Narrow Way that leads to life.<br>
I did answer you, those who believe do the will of the Father, they are the ones on the Narrow Path.<br>
Jeff the Finn<br>
