The Kingdom of God is the Narrow Way that leads to eternal life.  There is nothing in the Gospel that a verbal committment means anything at all, as St James pointed out faith without works is dead.  <br>
Nothing was straight forward that you provided, which by themselves seem fine but given the sermon on the Mount, means something totally different.  Of course to believe means to enter the Narrow Way, not doing that means you are on the broad road that leads to destruction.  <br>
So what is the problem?  You are told to forgive, and those who forgive will be forgiven, those who judge will be judged exactly like they have judged.  <br>
But as I have said salvation in Christ is given to everyone and not one person is outside of that salvation, only those who refuse the life of the Kingdom will be thrown out.  That means we have a part, in doing God's work.  You reject Jesus by refusing to do the work he told us to do.  To in Protestant terms accept Jesus means to do the works he told us to do.  As a Christian I know the Mercy of Our Lord covers Buddhists and Hindus and all of those outside of the Church, it is not my place to say they end up in hell, because His Mercy saved them as it has saved me.  <br>
